.Dd Nov 21, 2023
.Dt DHB 1
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm dhb
.Nd Print a number in decimal, hex, and binary
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Op Ar number
.Sh DESCRIPTION
Print a number in decimal, hexadecimal, and binary, and exit.
.Pp
Different numerical bases are idenified via prefixes. These prefixes are:
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It [none]
decimal (base 10)
.It 0x
hexadecimal (base 16)
.It 0b
binary (base 2)
.El
.Sh EXAMPLES
Convert from decimal:
.Dl $ dhb 123
.Bd -literal -offset indent -compact
	123     0x7B    0b1111011
.Ed
Convert from hexadecimal:
.Dl $ dhb 0x2F
.Bd -literal -offset indent -compact
        47      0x2F    0b101111
.Ed
Convert from binary:
.Dl $ dhb 0b111
.Bd -literal -offset indent -compact
         7      0x7    0b111
.Ed
